goals.question: What is the relationship between income and population?

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data.boxplot(column='income', by='region', figsize=(10,6))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of income across different regions?', wrap=True)
    plt.ylabel('Income')
    plt.xlabel('Region')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['income'], data['health'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Income')
    ax.set_ylabel('Health')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between health and income?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='population', ascending=False)
    plt.bar(data['country'], data['population'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the population distribution across different countries?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('country')['income'].mean().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values(by='income', ascending=False)
    plt.bar(data['country'], data['income'])
    plt.title('What is the average income by country?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('Country')
    plt.ylabel('Average Income')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
